abla}_{[X,Y]}s = 0 \ \ \  orall X,Y \in H.
\end{align} My instinct tells me the maximal non-integrability of H means that $	ilde{
abla}$ must be flat, but I can't prove this for myself or find a source. It is definitely sometimes true. For example one can define the obvious flat partial connection with respect to a trivialisation $\{e_i\}$ of $E$  egin{align}

